{
  "stem": "13469.4",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we had to be ready with a suitcase or a rucksack.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And it tells you in my book and  all of [INAUDIBLE] you can see what you had to prepare.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You had to have trousers, shirts, pullover, and warm clothes and shoes, and a mug and a fork and knife and spoon.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And it tells you all the things that you had to bring with you.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And you had to be prepared at all times for this eventuality.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It was more the food that was the difficult thing.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "All these other clothes kind of things we had ready for months, because these deportations by that time-- June '43, this was-- it had been going on for a year, where people had been either picked up in the street or volunteered, taken away according to lists or caught like this in roundups, cordoned-off areas.",
      "word_count": 55
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But that day was a very big one.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I believe that some 10,000 people were deported that day from Amsterdam.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It was a very big [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]-- one of the last.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Because my father, of course, immediately showed him his exemption from the [INAUDIBLE], but they said the exemptions were no longer valid kind of thing, and we had to go.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And he then tried the British nationality, and those people that came to the door apparently couldn't deal with that.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And they said, you'd have to deal with that later on.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And I know I can remember seeing my father arguing later on with higher officials, kind of thing, obviously about the British nationality of Eve, and all that sort of thing.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "But it didn't seem to help.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
